amendatorysection.para:
(a) Property delivered or shipped to a purchaser, other than
the United States Government, within this state regardless of the f.o.b. point
or other conditions of the sale;

(ii) The service,
when rendered, relates to tangible personal property located in this state
at the time the service is received;

(h) Net gains, but not less than zero, from
the sale of credit card receivables are in this state if the billing address
of the credit card holder is in this state;

(i) Gross receipts from the lease, rental,
or licensing of tangible personal property are in this state to the extent
the property is located in this state;
